snippet: The complaints raise the most serious questions yet about President Mohamed Morsi’s commitment to the rule of law and his ties to the Muslim Brotherhood.
abstract: Cairo prosecutor Mustafa Khater accuses aides to Egyptian Pres Mohamed Morsi of applying political pressure to investigation into bloody clashes outside presidential palace in order to corroborate Islamists' claims about conspiracy against president; Khater's complaints have raised serious questions about Morsi government’s commitment to impartial rule of law, as well as about its ties to Muslim Brotherhood
lead_paragraph: The complaints raise the most serious questions yet about President Mohamed Morsi’s commitment to the rule of law and his ties to the Muslim Brotherhood.

headline.main: Prosecutor Says Morsi Aides Interfered in Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Prosecutor Says Morsi Aides Interfered in Inquiry
